        IBComment:
          'The objectives and research questions are clearly stated and well-aligned with the focus of the study. However, the background and significance sections could be further enhanced by providing a deeper exploration of the context and a stronger justification for the study’s importance.',
        LRScore: 4,
        LRComment:
          'Your literature review presents several relevant theories, but the connections to your specific study are not deeply established. I recommend selecting and focusing on one core theory that directly supports your research focus, rather than referencing multiple frameworks that may not be fully aligned. Additionally, the Synthesis and Gap Identification section needs to emphasize more clearly why your study is critical, especially given the depth of existing research on motivation. Strengthening this will help clarify the unique contribution of your work.',
        MScore: 4,
        MComment:
          'You mentioned using pragmatism as your research paradigm, but it appears abruptly and without explanation or connection to your overall research approach. Pragmatism emphasizes practical, solution-focused inquiry and supports the use of multiple methods to address complex, real-world problems. However, you do not clarify how this paradigm influenced your “mystery box” action research study or how it guided your interactions and exploration with students. You need to clearly explain why pragmatism was appropriate for your study and how it shaped your methodology, data collection, and analysis. As it stands, the mention of pragmatism feels disconnected and underdeveloped, weakening the coherence and philosophical grounding of your research design. Be sure to explicitly link the paradigm to your mixed methods approach and show how it helped you make practical decisions throughout the research process.',
        RAScore: 3,
        RAComment:
          'You indicated that you measured student engagement levels and quantified them to represent pre- and post-intervention data. However, there is no clear explanation of the criteria or framework used to assess engagement, nor how the numerical values were generated. It remains unclear what specific indicators you used to define and measure engagement. The limitations of a study should not be included in the Results section. The Results section is meant to present the objective findings of the research. You mentioned conducting interviews as part of your data collection, but how the interview data contributed to your findings is unclear. In the Results section, you present two themes, but there is no indication whether these themes were derived from the interviews or another data source. It’s important to clearly explain how the interview data was analyzed and how it informed the development of your themes. Additionally, direct quotes or specific references to participant responses would help strengthen the connection between your data and your findings.',
        DScore: 4,
        DComment:
          "The discussion section summarizes the findings and links them to the theoretical framework, but it does not offer new insights or deeper interpretations. The findings presented are quite obvious and straightforward, limiting the discussion's analytical depth.",
