          'Since this is a traditional literature review, you should avoid personal experiences and references to your own research. Including such reflections is appropriate only when using an auto-ethnographic research design. In this case, the focus should remain on critically analyzing and synthesizing existing scholarly literature. In a standard literature review, it is important to avoid vague references like "A study published in The Journal of General Psychology (1995)." You need to name the study’s specific author(s)  and the year to establish academic credibility and allow readers to locate the source.',
