        RAComment:
          'The Findings section is clearly written, and the results are organized, thematic, and easy to follow. However, some areas need improvement. First, references to external literature should not be included in the results section; this space is reserved for presenting your data, not supporting it with citations. Second, when quoting directly from interviews, use proper formatting by placing the quote in italics and enclosing it in quotation marks or parentheses to distinguish participant voices clearly. Finally, avoid inserting your reflections or agreement with participants ( for example, saying "I agree with her"); this section should objectively report the findings without interpretation, which should be reserved for the discussion section.',
