          'Chapter 1 provided a clear presentation of the study. The researcher presented the research context in a logical and coherent manner. The research problem was identified and justified, and the study’s objectives and research questions were formulated accurately, with the topic being linked to a real classroom issue. The academic presentation was strong and highlighted the importance of differentiated instruction and innovative practices in early childhood education settings.\nHowever, the research gap was not sufficiently emphasized; it would have been helpful to clarify whether there were previous studies that specifically addressed the application of differentiated instruction and innovative practices in the context of kindergartens in the UAE.\nSome paragraphs could be divided into shorter ones to improve clarity and readability. It is recommended that the researcher add an independent paragraph titled "Research Gap" and reorganize some of the longer paragraphs to better support the logical flow of ideas.',
        LRScore: 4,
        LRComment:
          'The researcher presented a well-organized literature review that addressed differentiated instruction and innovative practices in kindergartens, with a clear connection drawn between recent studies and theoretical frameworks such as Dewey’s experiential learning theory and Vygotsky’s sociocultural theory. The literature was presented in a manner that supported the study’s objectives and demonstrated a good understanding of current challenges, such as the limited implementation of differentiated instruction and the need for interactive learning environments.\nHowever, the level of analytical critique of the literature was relatively limited, as the researcher primarily focused on presenting studies without sufficiently analyzing the points of agreement and divergence among them. Furthermore, the researcher did not thoroughly explain how the current study addresses existing research gaps. It is recommended that the researcher add brief critical paragraphs following each main theme to highlight comparisons between the findings and previous studies.',
        MScore: 5,
        MComment:
          'The researcher presented a well-structured description of the research methodology, clearly explaining the use of qualitative action research as a design appropriate to the nature of the study. The researcher detailed the tools employed, such as observation checklists, semi-structured interviews, and the analysis of student work, along with an explanation of the data analysis method using an objective interpretive approach, demonstrating a solid understanding of action research and its flexibility within classroom settings.\n\nIt would be preferable to expand the discussion on the challenges encountered during the implementation of the research, such as the flexibility of the intervention or real-time adjustments during execution. It is recommended that the researcher add a dedicated paragraph titled "Implementation Challenges" to strengthen the methodology section and to demonstrate a deeper awareness of the limitations of conducting research within real-world contexts.',
